Coronavirus map: Tracking the spread in the US and around the world The outbreak, which began in China, has sickened over 2.3 million worldwide.
By Saturday, the novel coronavirus outbreak in the United States had grown to more than 718,000 cases in all 50 states, the District of Columbia and Puerto Rico.
For more information on COVID-19 cases in your state, check your state's health department website, listed below.
